  "rendered": {
    "title": "Browser Use rebuild of changelog media and DeepSeek pricing support",
    "intro": "Today's nightly replaces the old screenshot pipeline with a Browser Use–driven changelog media system gated by independent quality and branding checks, and broadens model pricing coverage with new DeepSeek direct support and Fireworks open-model rates. Desktop builds for Mac, Windows, and Linux shipped alongside these changes.",
    "entries": [
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-1",
        "time_label": "2:34 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-24T09:34:25.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-24T12:02:56.000Z",
        "title": "Changelog media pipeline rebuilt on Browser Use",
        "summary": "The legacy screenshot pipeline was torn out and replaced with a Browser Use–first media system backed by seeded capture sessions and multi-stage quality gates.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Retired the old Browserbase-based screenshot workflows and their supporting demo-agent seeding code, replacing them with a Browser Use planning trial, an Aura navigation contract, and a new capture-login view; the server now exposes a dedicated capture_auth path so automated runs can authenticate without leaking secrets.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "888afbe54b40663a072507842a7e01418d213479",
              "a3be62e637dd8354ce1fb42228a562757e982f90"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Added independent branding and quality gates — raw screenshots, branded SVG cards, and final branded PNGs each pass their own structural and vision checks before anything is considered publish-ready.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "ff509bbaad88ca49ca6db28c3f157cb409d71a38",
              "36a29c577e5c6804bf89adf7092e62e2dda4bee6",
              "36ca8bb3bc141fd0735c1dac5ea2b5df923413f4"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Media runs now use seeded capture sessions passed through the URL fragment, with captureSession values redacted from task prompts and Browser Use message logs so secrets never land in artifacts.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "1fd2c56e3a21c05a700e8917d825c5cd59f26fad",
              "e7b602e4d46a22e9500212977b09f33b0506b409"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Hardened the planner so large changelogs are chunked instead of truncated, omitted entries get a rescue pass, and lower-priority candidates are recorded as explicit skips rather than silently dropped; added sharp for real image processing in branding.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "36ca8bb3bc141fd0735c1dac5ea2b5df923413f4",
              "9b716b4c5788798046f6f26a575cbc30eacbd3d2"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-2",
        "time_label": "5:09 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-24T12:09:13.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-24T12:09:13.000Z",
        "title": "Safer publish handoff for media runs",
        "summary": "A documented handoff step ensures media is only handed to publish after passing the full evaluator chain.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Extended the evaluator with a safe publish handoff stage and documented the gate in the Browser Use plan, so media only advances to publish after capture, branding, and vision checks all succeed.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "d2bd4beb584cde7593941416e78a0e4f0111cf78"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-3",
        "time_label": "9:45 AM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-24T16:45:12.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-24T18:53:18.000Z",
        "title": "Higher-resolution capture and Fireworks open-model pricing",
        "summary": "The media pipeline moved to 2560×1440 captures with a real publish script, and the server's fee schedule grew to cover Fireworks-hosted open models.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Bumped the desktop capture viewport to 2560×1440 (1920×1080 minimum), taught the Browser Use task to handle capture-secret prompts via sensitive-data placeholders, and reintroduced a proper publish-release-changelog-media workflow that chains off the changelog publish run with artifact-based metadata.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "24208c688c1a9dca28051ff193e32c85e4ec7a1b",
              "45351266085d051ff86ea89baaec5388be36c22f"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Added a high-resolution capture library and a real publish-changelog-media script with tests, wiring the evaluator, planner, and branding stages into a single end-to-end publishing path.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "45351266085d051ff86ea89baaec5388be36c22f"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Expanded the server fee schedule from 7 to 15 models, adding pricing for Kimi K2.5/K2.6 (including turbo and thinking variants), Kimi K2 Instruct 0905, DeepSeek V3.2, and GPT-OSS 120B, and taught model-ID normalization to handle Fireworks account and router prefixes.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "916e38bbf83f0defba37869fc495e9d0e4cd9f2d"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-4",
        "time_label": "1:49 PM",
        "started_at": "2026-04-24T20:49:30.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-04-24T20:58:01.000Z",
        "title": "DeepSeek direct provider support",
        "summary": "DeepSeek is now a first-class provider family with its own API key, default model, and usage accounting, while the older Fireworks-hosted DeepSeek V3.2 entry was retired from the model list.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Added DeepSeek as a recognized provider family with DEEPSEEK_API_KEY wiring, a deepseek-v4-flash default, and provider-family routing that distinguishes aura-deepseek-v4 direct models from the Fireworks-hosted aura-deepseek-v3-2 path.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "9e377b590455f455c962b3ffbab856a3671cb708"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Taught usage extraction to accept DeepSeek-style prompt_tokens, completion_tokens, and prompt_cache_hit/miss fields so benchmark pricing and token accounting work against DeepSeek's native API shape.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "9e377b590455f455c962b3ffbab856a3671cb708"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "Removed the Fireworks-hosted DeepSeek V3.2 model from the public model list now that direct DeepSeek access is available.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "dd65db9dfdeb24141f60b5bab966752b54ae24a4"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
